                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is reviewing the management plan for a client diagnosed with irritable bowel syndrome with predominant constipation (IBS-C). Which of the following primary health care provider (PHCP) orders would require a need for follow-up?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIrritable bowel syndrome (IBS) is a functional gastrointestinal (GI) disorder in which the client experiences dysfunctional bowel habits that can range from predominantly constipation (IBS-C), predominantly diarrhea (IBS-D), alternating episodes of constipation and diarrhea (IBS-A), or a mix of both episodes of diarrhea and constipation (IBS-M). Treatment varies, depending on the predominating symptoms the client is experiencing. For IBS-C, bulk-forming laxatives, such as psyllium that is taken with a glass of water at mealtimes and increased fluid intake of 8 to 10 glasses of water per day is recommended. Linaclotide is also given for IBS-C, as it promotes regular bowel movements. Loperamide is used in the treatment of IBS-D as this medication is an antidiarrheal and slows gastric motility to promote more solid bowel movements. Therefore, since this client is experiencing IBS-C, loperamide would not be appropriate and would exacerbate the client’s constipation even further. Therefore, option 3 requires a need for follow-up.",
                        "id": "ada5c78ddf3b4e7eb6903d594a8beecf",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "173dd434b0304e33b83ec4e466fd288e",
                                "content": "Urea breath test"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "7aaa3945522e42c4aa9de7d613e6c02c",
                                "content": "Chloride sweat test"
                            },
                            {
