                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIrritable bowel syndrome (IBS) is a functional gastrointestinal (GI) disorder in which the client may experience constipation, diarrhea, alternating constipation and diarrhea, or both. While the exact cause is unknown, environmental, immunological, genetic, hormonal, and stress factors play a role in the development of this disorder. Small intestine bacterial overgrowth may also play a factor in IBS. Abdominal pain and bloating may also be present, and abdominal pain commonly is localized to the left lower quadrant, although this is not necessarily always present. Therefore, option 2 is correct, as this would be the most likely quadrant for localized pain to occur with this disorder.",
