                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIrritable bowel syndrome (IBS) is a functional gastrointestinal (GI) disorder in which the client experiences dysfunctional bowel habits that can range from predominantly constipation (IBS-C), predominantly diarrhea (IBS-D), alternating episodes of constipation and diarrhea (IBS-A), or a mix of episodes of both diarrhea and constipation (IBS-M). Eliminate option 1 because IBS-C would be appropriate if the client were experiencing only constipation. Next, eliminate option 2 because IBS-D would be appropriate if the client were experiencing only diarrhea. Next, eliminate option 3 because IBS-M would be appropriate if the client were experiencing a mix of both diarrhea and constipation. IBS-A describes this client’s bowel habits, which were described as experiencing alternating episodes of diarrhea and constipation. Remember alternating and IBS-A. Therefore, option 4 is correct.",
